avdta.network.node

Class Merge

  • java.lang.Object
    • avdta.network.node.IntersectionControl
      • avdta.network.node.Merge

  • public class Merge
extends IntersectionControl
    This class implements Merge intersection control at a node.
    A merge is an intersection with more than one incoming links to a node and only one outgoing link.
    movements maps a link to a PhaseMovement through HashMap.
    Q_total stores the sum of the capacities of the incoming links to the merge.
    See Also:
    IntersectionControl

      • calculateFlow

        public void calculateFlow(java.util.List<Vehicle> sendingFlow)
        Calculates the flows to be moved. Starts a new time-step for each of the incoming links which involves reseting flow variables to zero after setting the leftovers to the fractional part of the current flow q i.e. left flow of the link from the last time-step.
        leftovers is the fractional part of the flow which couldn't move through the intersection because sending flow is an integer (one cannot move half a vehicle, for instance).
        Checks for each vehicle in sendingFlow if the current node is the destination, if not then vehicle count is added to sending flow S and also to S_rem (remaining sending flow of all the links combined) i.e load vehicles into sending flow.
        In the loop (while(R_rem > 0 && S_rem > 0)) flow from each incoming link is moved while the outgoing link can still receive flows and while there are flow still left to send. Note that the function calculateFlow only calculates the flows to be moved, the actual movement happens in step().
        Adds leftovers (from the previous time-step) of the incoming flows to their flows in next step.
        Parameters:
        sendingFlow - List of vehicles which can be sent in the current time-step.

      • step

        public int step()
        Implement movements at a merge for a time-step. exited is for counting the number of vehicles that have exited the link.
        Get vehicles on each incoming link of the merge and then add them to sending array list.
        Calculate the flow variables for this sending array list using calculateFlow(sending).
        For each of the vehicle in the array list check the next link for them in the route, if the current link is the last link exit them and update the exited count (also records the simulator time: exit_time = Simulator.time;) else calculate the equivalent flow of the vehicle and if there is available capacity then move the vehicle to the next link (removing the vehicle from the incoming links to the outgoing link of the merge node) and update the left flow of the phase movement of the link and also the receiving flow of the next link.
        Specified by:
        step in class IntersectionControl
        Returns:
        Returns the number of vehicle which has exited the network.
